      "routes": {
        "ekoberget-led-1": {
          "description": {
            "text": "Starts in the corner about 10 m left of För forna klätterfantaster. Some awkward bridging leads to a more technical finish.",
            "method": "llm",
            "model": "gpt-5.6-sol",
            "sourceIds": [
              "legacy:ekoberget"
            ]
          }
        },
        "ekoberget-led-2": {
          "description": {
            "text": "Starts on the slab immediately left of Namnlös. Fully bolted with an anchor.",
            "method": "llm",
            "model": "gpt-5.6-sol",
            "sourceIds": [
              "legacy:ekoberget"
            ]
          }
        },
        "ekoberget-led-3": {
          "description": {
            "text": "1 bolt + nuts.",
            "method": "llm",
            "model": "gpt-5.6-sol",
            "sourceIds": [
              "legacy:ekoberget"
            ]
          }
        },
        "ekoberget-led-4": {
          "description": {
            "text": "Anchor.",
            "method": "llm",
            "model": "gpt-5.6-sol",
            "sourceIds": [
              "legacy:ekoberget"
            ]
          }
        },
        "ekoberget-led-5": {
          "description": {
            "text": "Variant between För forna.. and Carnivore.",
            "method": "llm",
            "model": "gpt-5.6-sol",
            "sourceIds": [
              "legacy:ekoberget"
            ]
          }
        },
        "ekoberget-led-6": {
          "description": {
            "text": "Anchor.",
            "method": "llm",
            "model": "gpt-5.6-sol",
            "sourceIds": [
              "legacy:ekoberget"
            ]
          }
        },
        "ekoberget-led-7": {
          "description": {
            "text": "Trad + anchor. Note: only one bolt in the anchor.",
            "method": "llm",
            "model": "gpt-5.6-sol",
            "sourceIds": [
              "legacy:ekoberget"
            ]
          }
        },
        "ekoberget-led-8": {
          "description": {
            "text": "Anchor.",
            "method": "llm",
            "model": "gpt-5.6-sol",
            "sourceIds": [
              "legacy:ekoberget"
            ]
          }
        },
        "ekoberget-led-9": {
          "description": {
            "text": "New line right of Ekoturism. Anchor.",
            "method": "llm",
            "model": "gpt-5.6-sol",
            "sourceIds": [
              "legacy:ekoberget"
            ]
          }
        },
        "ekoberget-led-10": {
          "description": {
            "text": "Trad + anchor.",
            "method": "llm",
            "model": "gpt-5.6-sol",
            "sourceIds": [
              "legacy:ekoberget"
            ]
          }
        },
        "ekoberget-led-11": {
          "description": {
            "text": "Starts left of the large pine. An extra bolt now protects the previously rather scary finish.",
            "method": "llm",
            "model": "gpt-5.6-sol",
            "sourceIds": [
              "legacy:ekoberget"
            ]
          }
        },
        "ekoberget-led-12": {
          "description": {
            "text": "Starts between Lara and the pine and follows a corner feature. The route crosses Lara and shares its finish and anchor with Namnlös.",
            "method": "llm",
            "model": "gpt-5.6-sol",
            "sourceIds": [
              "legacy:ekoberget"
            ]
          }
        },
        "ekoberget-led-14": {
          "description": {
            "text": "Bolted crack. New top anchor from 2009.",
            "method": "llm",
            "model": "gpt-5.6-sol",
            "sourceIds": [
              "legacy:ekoberget"
            ]
          }
        },
        "ekoberget-led-15": {
          "description": {
            "text": "Joins Yohoia near the top.",
            "method": "llm",
            "model": "gpt-5.6-sol",
            "sourceIds": [
              "legacy:ekoberget"
            ]
          }
        },
        "ekoberget-led-16": {
          "description": {
            "text": "Anchor.",
            "method": "llm",
            "model": "gpt-5.6-sol",
            "sourceIds": [
              "legacy:ekoberget"
            ]
          }
        },
        "ekoberget-led-17": {
          "description": {
            "text": "Zigzags slightly.",
            "method": "llm",
            "model": "gpt-5.6-sol",
            "sourceIds": [
              "legacy:ekoberget"
            ]
          }
        },
        "ekoberget-led-18": {
          "description": {
            "text": "There is now a bolted left-hand finish. The grade is roughly the same.",
            "method": "llm",
            "model": "gpt-5.6-sol",
            "sourceIds": [
              "legacy:ekoberget"
            ]
          }
        },
        "ekoberget-led-19": {
          "description": {
            "text": "A nut-protected route, probably superseded by routes subsequently established on the same section of rock. Its exact line is unclear, however.",
            "method": "llm",
            "model": "gpt-5.6-sol",
            "sourceIds": [
              "legacy:ekoberget"
            ]
          }
        },
        "ekoberget-led-20": {
          "description": {
            "text": "Anchor.",
            "method": "llm",
            "model": "gpt-5.6-sol",
            "sourceIds": [
              "legacy:ekoberget"
            ]
          }
        },
        "ekoberget-led-21": {
          "description": {
            "text": "Trad. Beware of loose rock halfway up.",
            "method": "llm",
            "model": "gpt-5.6-sol",
            "sourceIds": [
              "legacy:ekoberget"
            ]
          }
        },
        "ekoberget-led-22": {
          "description": {
            "text": "Anchor.",
            "method": "llm",
            "model": "gpt-5.6-sol",
            "sourceIds": [
              "legacy:ekoberget"
            ]
          }
        },
        "ekoberget-led-23": {
          "description": {
            "text": "One of the finest routes at the crag. Sustained climbing on the beautiful pale wall. Anchor.",
            "method": "llm",
            "model": "gpt-5.6-sol",
            "sourceIds": [
              "legacy:ekoberget"
            ]
          }
        },
        "ekoberget-led-24": {
          "description": {
            "text": "Anchor.",
            "method": "llm",
            "model": "gpt-5.6-sol",
            "sourceIds": [
              "legacy:ekoberget"
            ]
          }
        },
        "ekoberget-led-25": {
          "description": {
            "text": "Follow the start of Wiwaxia to the ledge. Move slightly left and climb the pillar to Wiwaxia's anchor.",
            "method": "llm",
            "model": "gpt-5.6-sol",
            "sourceIds": [
              "legacy:ekoberget"
            ]
          }
        },
        "ekoberget-led-26": {
          "description": {
            "text": "After the slightly bouldery start, the climbing is superb all the way to the top. Shares an anchor with Mantra and Eldonia.",
            "method": "llm",
            "model": "gpt-5.6-sol",
            "sourceIds": [
              "legacy:ekoberget"
            ]
          }
        },
        "ekoberget-led-27": {
          "description": {
            "text": "New route left of Tvivlet. Anchor.",
            "method": "llm",
            "model": "gpt-5.6-sol",
            "sourceIds": [
              "legacy:ekoberget"
            ]
          }
        },
        "ekoberget-led-28": {
          "description": {
            "text": "Trad.",
            "method": "llm",
            "model": "gpt-5.6-sol",
            "sourceIds": [
              "legacy:ekoberget"
            ]
          }
        },
        "ekoberget-led-29": {
          "description": {
            "text": "Clip bolts 1, 2 and the top bolt on Pikaia. Between them, climb left of Pikaia's crux. Use a few handholds on Tvivlet before traversing back out to Pikaia's bulge at the top bolt. Protected with a few small cams and one nut. Anchor.",
            "method": "llm",
            "model": "gpt-5.6-sol",
            "sourceIds": [
              "legacy:ekoberget"
            ]
          }
        },
        "ekoberget-led-30": {
          "description": {
            "text": "Anchor.",
            "method": "llm",
            "model": "gpt-5.6-sol",
            "sourceIds": [
              "legacy:ekoberget"
            ]
          }
        },
        "ekoberget-led-31": {
          "description": {
            "text": "New route between Pikaia and Sannolikheten. Good, consistent climbing. Anchor.",
            "method": "llm",
            "model": "gpt-5.6-sol",
            "sourceIds": [
              "legacy:ekoberget"
            ]
          }
        },
        "ekoberget-led-32": {
          "description": {
            "text": "Trad.",
            "method": "llm",
            "model": "gpt-5.6-sol",
            "sourceIds": [
              "legacy:ekoberget"
            ]
          }
        },
        "ekoberget-led-33": {
          "description": {
            "text": "Starts left of Lögnen and heads towards a small overhang 5 metres above the ground, which is passed on the left. Continue straight up towards a protruding bulge, pass it on the right, then follow the easiest line to the top, continually trending right. Protected mainly with large and small cams, plus the odd nut.",
            "method": "llm",
            "model": "gpt-5.6-sol",
            "sourceIds": [
              "legacy:ekoberget"
            ]
          }
        },
        "ekoberget-led-34": {
          "description": {
            "text": "Trad.",
            "method": "llm",
            "model": "gpt-5.6-sol",
            "sourceIds": [
              "legacy:ekoberget"
            ]
          }
        },
        "ekoberget-led-35": {
          "description": {
            "text": "Anchor.",
            "method": "llm",
            "model": "gpt-5.6-sol",
            "sourceIds": [
              "legacy:ekoberget"
            ]
          }
        },
        "ekoberget-led-36": {
          "description": {
            "text": "Ferociously hard boulder start; perhaps it should be upgraded a notch? Anchor.",
            "method": "llm",
            "model": "gpt-5.6-sol",
            "sourceIds": [
              "legacy:ekoberget"
            ]
          }
        },
        "ekoberget-led-37": {
          "description": {
            "text": "Thomas Hansson's old project. 7b+/7c according to first ascensionist Johan.",
            "method": "llm",
            "model": "gpt-5.6-sol",
            "sourceIds": [
              "legacy:ekoberget"
            ]
          }
        },
        "ekoberget-led-38": {
          "description": {
            "text": "Anchor with only one ring.",
            "method": "llm",
            "model": "gpt-5.6-sol",
            "sourceIds": [
              "legacy:ekoberget"
            ]
          }
        },
        "ekoberget-led-39": {
          "description": {
            "text": "Anchor.",
            "method": "llm",
            "model": "gpt-5.6-sol",
            "sourceIds": [
              "legacy:ekoberget"
            ]
          }
        },
        "ekoberget-led-40": {
          "description": {
            "text": "Starts right of Pangea. Hard moves over the lip lead to a rest on the ledge. Finish up Pangea's slab. Anchor with only one ring.",
            "method": "llm",
            "model": "gpt-5.6-sol",
            "sourceIds": [
              "legacy:ekoberget"
            ]
          }
        },
        "ekoberget-led-41": {
          "description": {
            "text": "Trad.",
            "method": "llm",
            "model": "gpt-5.6-sol",
            "sourceIds": [
              "legacy:ekoberget"
            ]
          }
        },
        "ekoberget-led-42": {
          "description": {
            "text": "Trad.",
            "method": "llm",
            "model": "gpt-5.6-sol",
            "sourceIds": [
              "legacy:ekoberget"
            ]
          }
        },
        "ekoberget-led-43": {
          "description": {
            "text": "Starts about 10 m right of Pangea, just right of Vattenkammade snoken. An enjoyable and varied two-pitch route with comfortable belays.\n\n1. 6a, 20 m, 10 bolts: Easy climbing straight up a broken wall to a slab, trending left after the third bolt. Then easy climbing trends right to a small overhang, which is passed on the right, leading to a large, comfortable ledge with an anchor and abseil rings.\n\n2. 6a, 9 m, 5 bolts: Follow the ramp out right, then climb through a steeper section to a small ledge with an anchor and abseil rings. A 60 m rope is required to reach the ground from here in one abseil.",
            "method": "llm",
            "model": "gpt-5.6-sol",
            "sourceIds": [
              "legacy:ekoberget"
            ]
          }
        },
        "ekoberget-led-44": {
          "description": {
            "text": "Climbs straight up from Nattugglan's first belay. Climb straight up the corner, then left through an alcove and continue upwards, trending left to a small ledge with an anchor and abseil rings. A 60 m rope is required to reach the ground from here in one abseil.",
            "method": "llm",
            "model": "gpt-5.6-sol",
            "sourceIds": [
              "legacy:ekoberget"
            ]
          }
        },
        "ekoberget-led-45": {
          "description": {
            "text": "Good climbing in places, which could probably have been considered reasonably well protected with both large and small gear if only the rock had been completely solid. Dirty start in the corner, but soon moves right over a bulge to a wide crack (Camalot #5 useful). Follow the crack to a small ledge, step out right, climb the corner and then continue right for a few metres past the bushes before climbing straight up towards the slightly overhanging crack. A somewhat hidden micro-nut protects the climbing up to the crack.\n\nA shorter variant can be climbed by following a shallow crack from the ledge towards Nattugglan's first belay. The grade is then 5 or 5+.",
            "method": "llm",
            "model": "gpt-5.6-sol",
            "sourceIds": [
              "legacy:ekoberget"
            ]
          }
        }
      }
    }
  }
